race.comment: The big one of the day, which has brought together an interesting field. LE ZEBRA (2) is prepared by the trainers who won last year's Cup and he should be ready to go after a couple of runs back over 1400m. The step up to 1800m suits and he runs his best races when up on the speed so gate two could prove crucial. OCEAN BEYOND (3) turned in an eye-catching run over this journey last time, settling out the back before winding up late to finish 3 lengths away in fourth at Flemington. Should be doing best work late. CRAFTY BOSS (4) did his best work late and finished second last time over 1600m at Ararat, beaten a neck. Will trim down following recent racing. Capable of another bold effort. KOKORO (9) fought on to score a narrow win at Wycheproof over today's trip at his last appearance on November 1. Nice weight drop so he should run well.
